  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      MicroRNAs are important regulators of many cellular functions but their expression profile in
      human vitreous is still unclear. Aim of this study is to investigate microRNA expression
      profile by PCR in human vitreous of patients with various vitreoretinal disorders and compare
      with that of patients with macular holes which are suggested to be similar to that of healthy
      subjects.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
